  "texts": [
    "We can then again use the Hermitian analyticity of Dh,n (iη, k), and the fact that these differential operators are purely real for even n -|h| and purely imaginary for odd n -|h|, to conclude that this connected bulk-bulk propagator is anti-Hermitian analytic:G h n,S (C h n,S (η 1, η 2, -k *) * = -C h n,S (η 1, η 2, k).",
    "(C.23) JHEP05(2024)196A caution on locality and the anomaly of Hermitian analyticity.",
    "In all of the above proofs, locality of the general form of the interactions, meaning that the vertex operator D v is composed of derivatives but not inverse derivatives, is an implicit assumption.",
    "In momentum space, locality tells us that D v ∼ (ik) n is a polynomial in the energy variable k = |k| with n ∈ N. Such a local interaction vertex trivially satisfies Hermitian analyticity, i.e.",
    "D * v (-k) = D v (k), leading to (C.14) and the reality theorems."
